title: For Sale:  DAQ Quakenbush .458 big bore PCP air rifle
postcontent:
This is a very rare hand made rifle.  I believe that only a few hundred have been made.  You can purchase this rifle from Dennis Quakenbush cheaper than my asking price but you may have to wait years to get on his waiting list and then another year for one to be made.

I purchase this as a range toy but I will not be able to play for a few years because I decided to go back to university to complete a few more degrees.

The standard walnut stock is a work of art!  I can see no flaws on this gun.  It was removed from the shipping box  to take pictures and then was repackaged.  It is in mint, unfired condition.

Preppers love these air rifles.  You can take the largest american game with off the shelf(or out of the mold!) .45/70 bullets up to 500 grains.  If you have a supply of lead, a mold and fire, you will always be able to hunt when the SHTF.  You can fill either from a hand pump or a scuba tank.  The reservoir is rated for over 3000 PSI.

From the DAQ website...

"A 25” barrel, this rifle is 44” overall.  It weighs approximately 8lbs. 6oz.  The stock is familiar to tens of millions of shooters because the stock is the same shape and proportion of modern center fire rifles, like the Winchester model 70 and the Remington 700.

The LA Outlaw shoots a 430gr bullet at 732fps, which is 509fpe.  This rifle will produce two powerful shots from its reservoir on one fill.  It doesn’t need to be line fed from a scuba bottle, it doesn’t have the dependency of life support from a remote air source. 

The .458 cal. barrel is made expressly for airgun use.  It is not a firearm barrel.  This barrel has the correct rifling configuration and twist rate for an airgun.  I chose .458 cal. for this rifle so the shooter could use any of the ready-made bullets or bullet molds intended for use for the 45/70 cartridge.  Because the barrels are made from solid bar stock they are machined to the exact bore size without exception.  This way the standard size bullets fit the barrel; it is not some oddball caliber"

This is a cash, in person sale only to persons 18 years of age and older...this is NOT a toy.  I would take a partial trade...what do you have?  I do have permit as well as a C&R license.

WWII era Springfield Armory M1 Garand authentic U.S. Government rifle that has been inspected, headspaced and test fired for function.

title: For Sale/Trade:  West German Sig P226 Complete for parts 9mm
postcontent:
Long story short. I have owned this Sig for a long time. I dropped it off to have it Cerakoted and the smith fucked it up. The magazine release has a spring loaded pin that needs to be depressed before being removed. My guess the "smith" used a punch and knocked out the tiny portion of the frame the pin catches on. I had it rewelded but it was too soft and the release has since worked itself out. It worked flawlessly for the several hundred rounds before it failed again.

Its a shame because finding West German made sigs in good condition is getting harder to find. The pistol has had a trigger job and spring kit installed in the last couple years. I have even used it in IDPA occasionally at the Master level. 

You can use it for parts, or have a competent smith fix this very easily.  I just recently acquired a mk25 and x5 so I have decided to not pursue repairing this one.  From what I have seen just the complete slide and barrel sell for I think my price is more than fair for a complete pistol.

title: For Sale:  Arsenal SLR107CR AK47 rifle
postcontent:
I would like to offer for sale an Arsenal SLR-107CR rifle, you can read more about it at http://www.arsenalinc.com/usa/product.php?productid=47&cat=10&page=1, but in brief, factory Bulgarian stamped receiver, original Bulgarian chrome-lined barrel chambered in 7.62x39mm, rugged left-side folding stock, combination front sight post/gas block for 24mm muzzle devices, and correct 500m rear sight and pistol grip reinforcement plate.

The rifle has had 300 rounds of non-corrosive steel-cased ammo fired for sighting in and function checking. Sights are straight, action is smooth, very accurate. 

Finish is the stock Arsenal paint; in other words, looks great, but not particularly tough. There are scratches on the front sling attachment, small rub marks from MI rail and side rail usage, and wear in the usual spots from firing and manipulating the safety, but overall in very good condition.

Includes buttstock cleaning kit, 10-round Bulgarian waffle magazine, 30-round Combloc steel magazine, and Blue Force Gear AK sling.

If you are looking for a rugged, good-looking AK-47, don't miss the opportunity to pick this one up, as the 107CR has not been imported for many years and has become hard-to-find due to lack of supply. Perfect for shooting or showing off, very compact when you need to transport or store. 

Whether you are a new owner and want a top-shelf, factory-built rifle for your first AK or a long-time collector looking to fill a hole in your high-end military firearms collection, this rifle has something for you. Already has wonderful balance because of the combo FSP/GB, but would make a terrific SBR.

I live in Birmingham, but travel to Huntsville and Mobile regularly. I can provide proof (e.g. pistol permit) that I am a good guy and as many references as you need from recent firearms transactions. Deal with confidence. I won't waste your time, please don't waste mine.
